-- India's Central Bank Downgrades State Bank Rating to `B-', Mint Reports
-- B y   T h o m a s   A b r a h a m
-- 2010-11-12T01:23:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/india-s-central-bank-downgrades-state-bank-rating-to-b-mint-reports.html
The Reserve Bank of India downgraded
State Bank of India, the nation’s biggest lender, after the
central bank inspected the bank’s accounts for the year through
March 2009, the Mint reported, without saying where it obtained
the information. The rating based on capital, asset quality,
management, earnings, liquidity and systems and controls, was
lowered to “B-” from “B”, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
